UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Angela Lea SAENZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-50150

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 10, 2008. Joseph H. Gay, Jr., Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office Western District of Texas, San Antonio, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Angela Lea Saenz, pro se.

Before DAVIS, WIENER, and PRADO, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Angela Lea Saenz has moved for leave to *301withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Saenz has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be *301published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
